Australian stocks extend gains by close . Australian shares extended their gains in the afternoon to close higher on Friday as modest bargain hunting emerged after Thursday ' s weakness . The All Ordinaries index climbed 15 . 4 points to 2 , 362 . 1 . Brokers said the return of some buying confidence , as investors considered the yields on offer , had led to a stronger showing after Thursday ' s perverse reaction to the local interest rate reduction and Wall Street ' s surge . " It ' s quite an improvement , " said broker Robert Cameron of brokerage Cameron Securities , adding that the market seemed to be more settled after running ahead of itself ahead of Wednesday ' s rate cut . " There was probably an over - reaction ahead of the interest rate cut . People have settled down and adjusted to it and seen there is still some reasonable yields out there . " Standouts were few , although listed stockbroker McIntosh Securities caught the eye , jumping 15 cents to A $ 1 . 25 ( US $ 0 . 98 ) , its highest level since September 1994 , on speculation that U . S . broker Merrill Lynch was eyeing it as a takeover target . Near term outlook was seen mixed with much dependent on how the local market would weather a Wall Street correcting from its current record levels . Rises outnumbered falls by a ratio of about eight to five , while about 31 percent of stocks traded remained steady . ( A $ 1 = US $ 0 . 7840 ) 
